AC   P60266;
Toxin Css IV (CssIV).
"Scorpion toxins specific for Na+-channels.";
"Purification and chemical and biological characterizations of seven
toxins from the Mexican scorpion, Centruroides suffusus suffusus.";
-!- FUNCTION: Binds voltage-independently to sodium channels and shift
    the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials (By
    similarity).
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted protein.
-!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Expressed by the venom gland.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the long (4 C-C) scorpion toxin
    superfamily. Sodium channel inhibitor family. Beta subfamily.
Amidation; Direct protein sequencing; Ionic channel inhibitor;
Neurotoxin; Sodium channel inhibitor; Toxin.
